emails.subject: Understanding Usage Limits
emails.body:
Hi Taha,

AI usage on the platform is managed through daily limits.

Free access includes a set number of requests each day.
Limits refresh automatically after the reset period.

Higher limits are available through paid plans.

Best,
Billing Team

Spec-Driven Development focuses on planning before coding.

In this approach, specifications guide the development process.
This helps reduce errors and improves clarity.

Many modern AI workflows use this method to build reliable systems.

Kind regards,
Learning Team

emails.subject: What You Can Explore with Our Platform
emails.body:
Hi Taha,

Our platform supports multiple AI features designed for simplicity.

You can generate summaries, create quizzes, minimize code, and turn content
into study notes.
Each feature is designed to save time and reduce effort.

All tools are accessible from one dashboard, making learning smooth and
organized.

Regards,
Platform Team

emails.subject: Welcome to AI Studio
emails.body:
Hi Taha,

Welcome to AI Studio — a platform built for learning and experimenting with
AI.

AI Studio lets you explore different AI tools, test ideas, and understand
how models behave.
You can work with text, summaries, quizzes, and automation features.

Free users get limited usage each day.
Upgrading unlocks higher limits and advanced tools.

Best regards,
AI Studio Team

emails.subject: Need to take personal leave
emails.body:
Hi,

My mother just passed away unexpectedly last night. I'm completely
devastated and trying to make funeral arrangements. I don't know when I'll
be back in the office. I can't even think about work right now.

I need someone to take over my client presentation on Friday.

  Thanks,
  Taha Amin

emails.subject: Re: [contentlayerdev/contentlayer] Support NextJS 14 (Issue #575)
emails.body:
deCaldas left a comment (contentlayerdev/contentlayer#575)

@mohsentaleb 

**I was problems for building. Look**:

```sh
.contentlayer/generated/Authors/_index.mjs:3:63
Type error: ';' expected.

  1 | // NOTE This file is auto-generated by Contentlayer
  2 |
> 3 | import authors__defaultMdx from './authors__default.mdx.json' with { type: 'json' }
    |                                                               ^
  4 |
  5 | export const allAuthors = [authors__defaultMdx]
  6 |
Next.js build worker exited with code: 1 and signal: null
```
So. I run `npm install contentlayer next-contentlayer date-fns --legacy-peer-deps` and problem resolve.

**Thanks**


--
